{"word":"αὐλέω","slug":"αὐλέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>αὐλέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:αὐλός'><el>αὐλός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to play on the flute</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>αὐλ. ἔξοδον</el> <i>to play</i> a finale, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, of tunes, <i>to be played on the flute</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; but, <el>αὐλεῖται μέλαθρον</el> <i>is filled with music</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> also of persons, <i>to be played to, hear music</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}